# CMS Page Builder — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A fully functional **Dynamic CMS Page Builder** integrated into the admin dashboard at the `CMS Builder` sidebar tab.

## Changes Summary

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| **Supabase** `dynamic_pages` table | New table with JSONB content, RLS, 6 seeded pages |
| [actions.ts](file:///c:/Users/Omar/Desktop/k3%20store/storefront-nextjs/app/%5Blocale%5D/admin/actions.ts) | +3 server actions: [saveDynamicPage](file:///c:/Users/Omar/Desktop/k3%20store/storefront-nextjs/app/%5Blocale%5D/admin/actions.ts#172-189), [createDynamicPage](file:///c:/Users/Omar/Desktop/k3%20store/storefront-nextjs/app/%5Blocale%5D/admin/actions.ts#190-210), [deleteDynamicPage](file:///c:/Users/Omar/Desktop/k3%20store/storefront-nextjs/app/%5Blocale%5D/admin/actions.ts#211-220) |
| [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Omar/Desktop/k3%20store/storefront-nextjs/app/%5Blocale%5D/admin/page.tsx) | Fetches `dynamic_pages` and passes to [AdminLayout](file:///c:/Users/Omar/Desktop/k3%20store/storefront-nextjs/app/%5Blocale%5D/admin/client-components.tsx#50-266) |
| [client-components.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Omar/Desktop/k3%20store/storefront-nextjs/app/%5Blocale%5D/admin/client-components.tsx) | Added `site-settings` tab type, sidebar entry, renders [SiteSettingsTab](file:///c:/Users/Omar/Desktop/k3%20store/storefront-nextjs/app/%5Blocale%5D/admin/site-settings-tab.tsx#303-655) |
| [site-settings-tab.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Omar/Desktop/k3%20store/storefront-nextjs/app/%5Blocale%5D/admin/site-settings-tab.tsx) | **[NEW]** ~480-line CMS builder component |
| [globals.css](file:///c:/Users/Omar/Desktop/k3%20store/storefront-nextjs/app/globals.css) | Added `.no-scrollbar` + toast animation |

## Features Implemented

- **Dynamic Page Tabs** — DB-driven (Home, About Us, B2B Portal, Products, Contact, Footer), `+` to add, trash to delete
- **Section CRUD** — Add, delete, visibility toggle, up/down reorder
- **Rich Text Editor** — Bold, Italic, Underline, Lists, **Link dialog** (with URL + display text), Image insert
- **Media Upload** — Drag & drop to Supabase Storage `public_assets`, replace/remove overlay
- **Save & Publish** — Upserts full JSONB to Supabase, success/error toast
- **Discard Changes** — Resets to last DB state with confirmation
- **Responsive** — Sticky action bar, mobile FAB, scrollable tabs

